Title: Night Window
Credit: Written with Scriptboard
Author: Scriptboard Example
Draft date: 2026-04-18

INT. APARTMENT - NIGHT

A narrow room. Laptop glow. Rain against the window.

LEON sits at a desk, replaying a voice note he cannot bring himself to delete.

PHONE SPEAKER
You do not have to answer tonight.
You just have to decide whether you are staying.

Leon stops the playback.

EXT. STREET BELOW - NIGHT

Headlights slide across wet asphalt.
A tram sighs at the corner.

Leon appears at the window, looking down at the city as if it might answer for him.

INT. APARTMENT - LATER

A blank document fills the screen.
He types a single line.

LEON
I stayed long enough to hear the room go silent.

He saves the file, closes the laptop, and finally exhales.

FADE OUT.
